OL,3,CNorth Sea sandstone could be used to
OL,4,Cstore carbon dioxide, report says
OL,6,FSandstone beneath the North Sea could
OL,7,Fbe used to store carbon dioxide, a new
OL,8,Fstudy has claimed.
OL,10,FThe British Geological Survey (BGS)
OL,11,Freport shows how sandstone beneath the
OL,12,FNorth Sea could assist with the UK's
OL,13,Fplans for carbon capture and storage
OL,14,F(CCS).
OL,16,FCCS encompasses a range of
OL,17,Ftechnologies designed to significantly
OL,18,Freduce emissions from large industrial
OL,19,Fsources such as steelworks, cement
OL,20,Fplants and thermal power stations.
