OL,3,CNorth Sea sandstone could be used to
OL,4,Cstore carbon dioxide, report says
OL,6,FDespite accounting for approximately
OL,7,F60% of the UK's total estimated carbon
OL,8,Fdioxide storage capacity, the central
OL,9,FNorth Sea remains under-represented
OL,10,Ffor long-term storing of carbon
OL,11,Fdioxide.
OL,13,FKey considerations for the BGS include
OL,14,Flooking at the degree of connectivity
OL,15,Fbetween sandstone units, which has a
OL,16,Fbearing on pressure during CO2
OL,17,Finjection, and balancing between
OL,18,Fpressure dissipation and pressure
OL,19,Finterference between neighbouring
OL,20,Fstorage sites, which affects storage
OL,21,Fcapacity.
