OL,3,CNorth Sea sandstone could be used to
OL,4,Cstore carbon dioxide, report says
OL,6,FMichelle Bentham, chief scientist for
OL,7,Fdecarbonisation and resource
OL,8,Fmanagement at BGS, said: "From the
OL,9,Flate 1990s to the early 2000s, BGS
OL,10,Fundertook pioneering work to evaluate
OL,11,Fthe potential to reduce greenhouse gas
OL,12,Femissions by storing CO2 in rocks
OL,13,Foffshore UK, to help mitigate climate
OL,14,Fchange and develop clean energy.
OL,16,F"This early work focused on the
OL,17,Fgeological storage opportunities in
OL,18,Fthe southern North Sea and east Irish
OL,19,FSea regions.
