OL,3,CNorth Sea sandstone could be used to
OL,4,Cstore carbon dioxide, report says
OL,6,F"Potential storage sites in these
OL,7,Fregions, first identified by BGS, are
OL,8,Famong the first to be licensed and
OL,9,Fpermitted by the NSTA (North Sea
OL,10,FTransition Authority) for CO2 storage.
OL,12,F"For the UK to reach its ambition of
OL,13,Fstoring 170 million tonnes of CO2 a
OL,14,Fyear by 2050, it will need to look
OL,15,Fbeyond the current well-appraised
OL,16,Fgeographical areas.
OL,18,F"The stacked sandstones of the central
OL,19,FNorth Sea are relatively under-
OL,20,Fstudied, with huge CO2 storage
OL,21,Fpotential.
